Consider the folllowing code:

Module A:

```typescript
const REGISTRY: { [name: string]: any } = {};

export function MyComp (name: string) {
  return function (compType: any) {
    REGISTRY[name] = compType;
  }
}

export function regLog() { return Object.keys(REGISTRY).length }
```
Module B:

```typescript
@MyComp('myComp')
@Component({template: '!'})
export class MyComp implements OnInit {
  ngOnInit() { 
    console.log(regLog());
  }
}
```

Building with angular.json aot: false works, while building with AoT does not. Setting the buildOptimizer to false, works for declarations in module A but ignore module B.

Hi,

I try to get "false" when the toggle is disabled currently I have a "null".

I found here that this is supposed to overwrite the default value:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56108213/how-to-disable-the-drag-option-on-angular-material-slide-toggle-component

```
import { MAT_SLIDE_TOGGLE_DEFAULT_OPTIONS } from '@angular/material';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-selector',
  templateUrl: './template.html',
  providers: [
    {provide: MAT_SLIDE_TOGGLE_DEFAULT_OPTIONS , useValue: {disableToggleValue: false, disableDragValue: true}},
  ]
})
```

But I continue to get null when it's inactived and true when it's activated.

Any Idea?
